  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "First-person Grey Knights novel narrated in retrospect by Hyperion of Squad Castian, covering the chapter's part in the First War of Armageddon and the intra-Imperium fallout remembered as the Months of Shame. Hyperion grows up inside Castian under Justicar Galeo as the squad's daemon-eradication work pulls them across the war and the warp around it. Annika Jarlsdottir — a Fenrisian Inquisitor whose home-world loyalty to Logan Grimnar's Space Wolves collides with Grey Knights methods — anchors the Inquisition end and brings the chapter into a later confrontation with the Wolves over the fate of Armageddon's survivors. Somber and reflective rather than action-march: incorruptible but not infallible, the moral cost is the load-bearing spine.",
